results.name: Number of noncrossing path sets on n nodes with each path having a prime number of nodes.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..500
mathematica: seq[n_] := InverseSeries[x/(1 + Sum[If[PrimeQ[k], k*2^(k-3)*x^k, 0], {k, 2, n}]) + O[x]^(n+2), x]/x;
CoefficientList[seq[28], x] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, May 15 2018, translated from PARI *)
program: (PARI) seq(n)={Vec(serreverse(x/(1 + sum(k=2, n, if(isprime(k), k*2^(k-3)*x^k))) + O(x^(n+2)) )/x)}
